This paper deals with the analysis of algorithms for online paging, which is a topic in computer science that falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves the use of probabilistic analysis and optimization, which are relevant to information theory (cs.IT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The analysis of the algorithms' performance on different input distributions also involves statistical and machine learning techniques, which are relevant to the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and cryptography (cs.CR).
